{meta: title Believe Another's Lips}
{meta: artist Sonny James}
{meta: composer Jimmie Loden}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]If you believe another’s [C7]lips 
You know how much I [F]care
[G7]If they repeat the things I say
They’ll tell you that I’m [C]fair
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
For you must hear it from their lips
How much I love you [F]dear
[G7]And how I try to live for you
Each day of every [C]year
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I’ve even tried to write [F]a song
To tell you how [C]I feel
With words and music from the [A7]heart
[D7]To prove my love is [G7]real
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]If anybody tells you 
That I’ll always be true [F]blue
[G7]Then please believe another’s lips
When they say I love [C]you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
And though I may not [F]equal
All you think I ought to [C]be
I hope your loving heart will [A7]hold 
A [D7]special place for [G7]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[C]I may not have the courage dear
To say these things [F]to you
[G7]But please believe another's lips
When they say I love [C]you
{end_of_verse}
